div.div: YY contains information about 9 cases, each one of these 9 cases contains the most meaningful information over a 2×22 \times 2 region. And each value of these 2×22 \times 2 regions contains information about 9 pixels from the input image... All in all the YY value focus on a region of size 6×66 \times 6. Actually, we could even say that YY contains information about a region of size 8×88 \times 8 if we account for the padding before the first convolution
